  "prompt": "Can I take Nyquil and Benadryl at the same time?",
  "response": "It is generally not recommended to take Nyquil and Benadryl together without consulting a healthcare professional. Both medications contain antihistamines and can cause drowsiness, which may lead to:\n\n1. Increased sedation\n2. Potential overdose of antihistamines\n3. Enhanced side effects\n\nSpecific risks include:\n- Extreme drowsiness\n- Impaired coordination\n- Potential respiratory depression\n\nAlways consult with a doctor or pharmacist before combining medications, especially if you have any pre-existing medical conditions or are taking other medications.\n\nIf you're experiencing multiple symptoms, ask a healthcare professional about the safest way to manage them.",
